<td>
<h2 style="text-align:center;"><FONT COLOR=#800000><B>Zabaglione wth Berries</B></FONT></h2>
<hr size="4" width="100%" align="Center" >
<p align="center"><img border="0" src="http://www.great-chicago-italian-recipes.com/images/bigstockphoto_berry_smallest.jpg" width="150" height="225" alt=""></p>
<hr size="4" width="100%" align="Center" >
<font color=#800000><b>BERRY GOOD DESSERT</b></font><p><b>Zabaglione </b> is a light creamy Italian treat made with deliciously sweet Marsala wine.<TABLE align="right" width="300">    <TR><TD><script type="text/javascript"><!--
google_ad_client = "pub-7670029976119966";
/* 300x250, created 3/4/10 */
google_ad_slot = "7231243739";
google_ad_width = 300;
google_ad_height = 250;
//--></script><script type="text/javascript"
src="http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js"></script></TD></TR></TABLE></p><p></p><p>This dessert is simple to make and can be easily flavored in a variety of different ways.  Just add some different liquors like Amaretto di Saronno or Frangelico to enhance this already   wonderful dessert.<br><br></p><p>This Venetian specialty will compliment any Italian dinner.  Served in a martini or wine glass topped with fresh raspberries, blueberries or strawberries this dessert will turn your dining table into an elegant masterpiece.<br><br><table align="right">  <tr>  <td><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="120" style="background-color: #ffffff;">    <tr>      <td align="center" valign="middle"><a id="ProductLink0" href="http://affiliates.art.com/get.art?T=15052709&A=945987&L=8&P=10117793&S=2&Y=0" target="_blank"><img id="Product0" border="0" alt="Buy at Art.com" src="http://images.art.com/images/products/regular/10117000/10117793.jpg"align="right" width="180" height="225"></a></td></p><p>    </tr>    <tr>      <td align="center" valign="middle" style="font-family:verdana, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:10px;color:#000000;" ><a id="BuyLink0" href="http://affiliates.art.com/get.art?T=15052709&A=945987&L=8&P=10117793&S=2&Y=0" target="_blank">Buy From Art.com</a></td>    </tr>  </table>  </td></tr></table><font color=#800000><b>INGREDIENTS</b></font></p><p><li>6 to 8 egg yolks<li>1/4 cup of sugar<li>1/2 cup of sweet Marsala wine<li>1 oz. of your favorite liquor (optional) <li><blueberries, raspberries, strawberries <li>whipped cream<br><br></p><p><font color=#800000><b>PREPARATION</b></font></p><p><li>In the top part of a double boiler or a metal bowl, mix the sugar and egg yolks together using a mixer or whisk until creamy.<li>Slowly mix in the Marsala and the liquor if desired.<li>Place on top of a simmering pot of water and whisk until custard is thick.<li>Make sure the water is not boiling so not to cook the eggs.</p><p>Spoon into a glass and top with whipped cream and berries and serve warm.</p><p>For a lighter dessert just mix some whipped cream into the custard.<br><br></p><p></p><p><div id="links" style="position:absolute; top:1350px; margin-left:-141px; width:120px; z-index:789;"></p><p><br><br><script type="text/javascript"><!--
google_ad_client = "pub-7670029976119966";
/* 120x240, created 8/26/10 */
google_ad_slot = "4717118541";
google_ad_width = 120;
google_ad_height = 240;
//--></script><script type="text/javascript"
src="http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js"></script><br><br><a href="http://www.cafepress.com/italian_recipes"><img src="http://www.great-chicago-italian-recipes.com/images/greatchicago_small.jpg" target="new" align="center" height="104" width="122" alt="logo" border="2"></a><center>Cafepress<br><br><a href="http://click.linksynergy.com/fs-bin/click?id=BpWEAVClD3E&offerid=133988.10000568&type=4&subid=0"><IMG alt="My Wines Direct Wine Clubs - The Perfect Gift" border="0" src="http://affiliates.mywinesdirect.com/banners/clubs/club-125x125.jpg"></a><IMG border="0" width="1" height="1" src="http://ad.linksynergy.com/fs-bin/show?id=BpWEAVClD3E&bids=133988.10000568&type=4&subid=0"><br><br><iframe src="http://rcm.amazon.com/e/cm?t=greachicitalr-20&o=1&p=21&l=ur1&category=gourmet&banner=1HN0SQGXKCCJ4YE167G2&f=ifr" width="125" height="125" scrolling="no" border="0" marginwidth="0" style="border:none;" frameborder="0"></iframe></div></p><p></p><p><TABLE align="center" width="468">    <TR><TD><script type="text/javascript"><!--
